# Fail Fast

## Philosophy

Detect and report errors as early as possible. Do not silently swallow or defer failures.

## Input Validation

```java
// ✅ GOOD - fail immediately with clear message
public void setAmount(int amount) {
    if (amount <= 0) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("amount must be positive, got: " + amount);
    }
    this.amount = amount;
}

// ❌ BAD - silent or deferred failure
public void setAmount(int amount) {
    if (amount <= 0) return;  // Silent ignore
    this.amount = amount;
}
```

## Null Safety

```java
// ✅ GOOD
public void process(Player player) {
    Objects.requireNonNull(player, "player cannot be null");
    // ...
}

// ❌ BAD
public void process(Player player) {
    if (player == null) return;  // Hides bug; caller should fix
}
```

## Configuration & Startup

- Validate `plugin.yml`, `config.yml`, and required resources in `onEnable()`
- If critical config is missing or invalid, call `getLogger().severe(...)` and `getServer().getPluginManager().disablePlugin(this)` then return
- Never start with broken state; fail during enable

## Exceptions

- Do not catch and ignore; log and rethrow or handle meaningfully
- Use specific exception types; avoid generic `Exception`
- Include context in error messages (what failed, expected vs actual)
